title: High Government Investment in Primary Education
description: In 2015, Serbia allocated 43.65% of its GDP per capita to government expenditure per student in primary education, indicating a strong commitment to educational development.

title: Empowerment in Women's Health Decisions
description: By 2019, 96.2% of Serbian women aged 15-49 were making informed decisions regarding sexual relations, contraceptive use, and reproductive health care, showcasing significant progress in women's empowerment.

title: Low Multidimensional Poverty Rate
description: In 2019, only 0.1% of Serbia's population was living in multidimensional poverty, reflecting effective poverty alleviation strategies.

title: Minimal Deaths by Injury
description: In 2019, injuries accounted for just 2.37% of total deaths in Serbia, indicating effective public safety and health measures.

title: Negative Net Aid Flows from Finland
description: In 2022, Serbia experienced a negative net bilateral aid flow of -$4,099,999.90 from Finland, suggesting a reduction in financial support from this donor.

title: Negative Official Flows from UNECE
description: In 2015, Serbia had a negative net official flow of -$961.99 from UN agencies, specifically UNECE, indicating a decrease in financial assistance from this source.
